===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To amuse (someone); {{non-gloss definition|said especially of a professional [[entertainer]]}}.
#: ''The motivational speaker not only instructed but also '''entertained''' the audience.''
# {{transitive|and|intransitive}} To have someone over at one's home for a party or visit.
#: ''They enjoy '''entertaining''' a lot.''
# {{transitive}} To have a thought in mind.
#: ''The committee would like to '''entertain''' the idea  of reducing the budget figures.''

